<a name="times"><h2>Upcoming times for a stop</h2></a>
<p>
	To get times go to the following address: <br />
	<pre>
/times/&lt;route#&gt;/&lt;stop&gt;/&lt;direction&gt;
		</pre>
	Fill in the proper information for each part and be sure to make sure that all spaces and periods are removed from the stop and direction.
	Don't worry about capitilization as the seach is agnostic to capitalization.
	If you want the JSON response just add &quot;.json&quot; to the end of the URI.  
	<br/>
	<br/>
	An example of a good JSON response is as follows:
	<pre>
{
   "status":"GOOD",
   "currentTime":"3/29/2012 6:27:42 PM",
   "data":
   {
      "stop":"Alabama &amp; Broad St.",
      "direction":"Northbound",
      "lat":33.7534757,
      "lon":-84.3920023,
      "route":1,
      "times":["6:45 PM","7:30 PM","8:15 PM"]
   }
}
		</pre>
	<br/>
	An example of a JSON response to a failure is as follows:
	<pre>
{
   "status":"FAIL",
   "currentTime":"3/29/2012 6:33:39 PM",
   "data":
   {
      "Error":
      {
         "message":"Stop not found"
      }
   }
}
		</pre>
</p>
