<a name="bus"><h2>Bus location</h2></a>
<p>
	To get all buses on a particular route go to the following URI:
	<pre>
/bus/&lt;route#&gt;
	</pre>
	Fill in the route number with a valid route and the information about all buses on that route will be returned.
	For a JSON response add &quot;.json&quot; to the end of the URI.
	<br/>
	<br/>
	A successfull JSON response will look like the following:
	<pre>
{
   "status":"GOOD",
   "currentTime":"3/30/2012 2:56:23 AM",
   "data":
   [
      {
      	"lat":"33.7907535",
        "lon":"-84.4418383",
        "num":2501,
        "next_stop":"Destination reached",
        "route":3,
        "direction":"Southbound"
       }
   ]
}
	</pre>
	A JSON error response will look like the following:
	<pre>
{
   "status":"FAIL",
   "currentTime":"3/29/2012 6:33:39 PM",
   "data":
   {
      "Error":
      {
         "message":"No buses currently on route 1"
      }
   }
}	
	</pre>
</p>

