<a name="astops"><h2>All bus stops for a given route</h2></a>
<p>
	To get all the bus routes (520 and 521 currently aren't in there) go to the following address:
	<pre>
/stops/&lt;route#&gt;		
	</pre>
	All you need to do is just supply the route number after stops and you will get all the stops for that route.  Just add 
	&quot;.json&quot; to the end of the URI to get a json response.
	<br/>
	An example of a good JSON response is as follows:
	<pre>
{
   "status":"GOOD",
   "currentTime":"3/29/2012 10:18:09 PM",
   "data":
   [
      {
      	"stop":"Alabama & Broad St.",
      	"direction":"Northbound",
      	"lat":33.7534757,
      	"lon":-84.3920023,
      	"route":1,
      	"times":["10:30 PM","11:15 PM","12:00 AM"]
      },
      {
      	"stop":"Luckie St & North Ave.",
      	"direction":"Northbound",
      	"lat":33.7704466,
      	"lon":-84.3961869,
      	"route":1
      	"times":["10:41 PM","11:26 PM","12:11 AM"]
      },
      ...
   ]
}
	</pre>
	<br/>
	An example of a JSON response to a failure is as follows:
	<pre>
{
   "status":"FAIL",
   "currentTime":"3/29/2012 6:33:39 PM",
   "data":
   {
      "Error":
      {
         "message":"Stop not found"
      }
   }
}
	</pre>
</p>
